The Edgecliff Centre, 203-233 New South Head Road

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE and Karbon Property are pleased to offer to the market The Edgecliff Centre. One of the most prominently located mixed-use buildings in Sydney’s Eastern Suburbs positioned adjacent to Edgecliff Railway Station and Bus Interchange.  

Situated just 3.5kms from the Sydney CBD, the Edgecliff Centre offers numerous opportunities to commercial tenants wishing to be located perfectly between the CBD and Eastern Suburbs. 

Spaces available vary from fitted and non-fitted out options. A mixed-use building with ground floor retail and 6 floors of commercial office, the building links directly to the Edgecliff Transport Interchange with food, speciality retail, transport, café’s and supermarket all located under the commercial floors. 

Features include:
- Private offices – control your environment and feel safe in the office at pricing below that of co-working
- Open plan and modular office options available
- Offices with private boardroom and kitchen facilities also available
- Flexible terms
- Common board room facilities available
- Prime location, directly above Edgecliff Train Station
- Parking available
- Examples of Availability: 55sqm, 90sqm, 130sqm, 160sqm, 190sqm and above (approx)
- Great natural light
- Prominent business address
- Convenience – Aldi, Westpac, Newsagent, BWS, Hairdressers and a Pharmacy


For more information or to organise an inspection, please reach out to one of the agents below:

CBRE:

Fergus.bowen@cbre.com


Karbon:
